what is drupal and where can i get it stanford answers stanford university stanford answers what is drupal and where can i get it categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home what is drupal and where can i get it search this site drupal is a free software package that allows an individual or a community of users to publish manage and organize many different kinds of content on a website go to drupal org for information support forums and downloads note drupal requires a mysql database mysql is not available to everyone at stanford the mysql service is available to organizations that have an afs directory in afs ir dept afs ir group afs ir class or afs ir dist web services individual users are not eligible for the service you must have a full sunetid account and write access permissions to the afs directory allocated for your department or group to check your eligibility login to a unix timeshare machine such as cardinal stanford edu and type one of the following to see a list of group names or sunetid names that have access to the directory cd afs ir dept department name or cd afs ir group group name or cd afs ir dist web services service name fs listacl web collaboration tools drupal stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
